Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-red; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with part-preserved symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Klenostratos. Seems to have been very badly trimmed; therefore presumably from Naukratis. Month name may begin with pi; close to Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0164.28 (Panamou), but probably not the same die.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1129)
